1230
01:26:04,300 --> 01:26:08,300
Its on the side of my motorcycle
over there, thats my lucky number.

1231
01:26:08,500 --> 01:26:11,399
Have you registered?

1232
01:26:11,400 --> 01:26:13,899
No, thats what
I've come over for.

1233
01:26:13,900 --> 01:26:16,499
These two blokes sent me over here,
Mike and someone else.

1234
01:26:16,500 --> 01:26:19,099
Sir, registration closed
last month.

1235
01:26:19,100 --> 01:26:23,100
If you haven't registered,
I'm sorry, you just can't run.

1236
01:26:25,400 --> 01:26:28,499
I can't run?

1237
01:26:28,500 --> 01:26:31,734
Well, how was I supposed to know
I should have pre-registered?

1238
01:26:31,735 --> 01:26:33,951
I've come a heck of a long way
to ride my bike.

1239
01:26:33,952 --> 01:26:36,099
I'm not going anywhere
until I've done just that.

1240
01:26:36,100 --> 01:26:39,399
I've come all the way from New Zealand,
you know. Its a long way.

1241
01:26:39,400 --> 01:26:41,299
Look, mister,
we don't make the rules.

1242
01:26:41,300 --> 01:26:44,734
An event like this doesn't just happen
in one day, rules are rules.

1243
01:26:44,735 --> 01:26:46,699
Entries closed July 31st.

1244
01:26:46,700 --> 01:26:50,700
Well, crikey, I live in Invercargill,
its half way round the bloody earth.

1245
01:26:51,000 --> 01:26:53,734
How was I supposed to know these things?
I didn't know all this stuff.

1246
01:26:53,735 --> 01:26:55,099
Sir, its not our problem.

1247
01:26:55,100 --> 01:26:57,734
I thought I could just turn up here
and have my bike timed.

1248
01:26:57,735 --> 01:27:01,735
- You don't have to call me...
- Well, you thought wrong.

1249
01:27:10,000 --> 01:27:12,599
Jim Moffatt!

1250
01:27:12,600 --> 01:27:15,699
Its Burt, Burt Munro.
Can you come over here, mate?

1251
01:27:15,700 --> 01:27:17,799
I'll be right back.

1252
01:27:17,800 --> 01:27:19,699
I need a bit of help.

1253
01:27:19,700 --> 01:27:21,599
Hey, Burt. Whats up?

1254
01:27:21,600 --> 01:27:25,499
Well, I have these blokes telling
me I can't run my bike...

1255
01:27:25,500 --> 01:27:27,799
because I'm not pre-registered.

1256
01:27:27,800 --> 01:27:30,399
- You didn't register?
- No, I didn't know anything about it.

1257
01:27:30,400 --> 01:27:33,199
You know how it is Jim,
rules are rules.

1258
01:27:33,200 --> 01:27:37,200
- You should have registered months ago.
- I didn't know.

1259
01:27:37,800 --> 01:27:40,499
I'll have a talk with these guys later,
see if I can change their minds.

1260
01:27:40,500 --> 01:27:44,099
- Your blooïs worth bottling.
- I don't know about that.

1261
01:27:44,100 --> 01:27:46,099
Look,
we can talk about this later.

1262
01:27:46,100 --> 01:27:48,099
Maybe you can let him go
through tech inspection.

1263
01:27:48,100 --> 01:27:52,100
Get that out of the way?
Just in case we can let him ride.

1264
01:27:52,400 --> 01:27:55,399
You're asking a lot.

1265
01:27:55,400 --> 01:27:59,400
Alright.

1266
01:28:00,500 --> 01:28:02,299
- Okay.
- Alright.

1267
01:28:02,300 --> 01:28:04,699
- Make me proud.
- Thanks a lot.

1268
01:28:04,700 --> 01:28:08,700
You give me a bit
of a fright there.

1269
01:28:11,500 --> 01:28:14,699
You know these don't look
like high speed tyres.

1270
01:28:14,700 --> 01:28:17,099
Well, they are high speed tyres.

1271
01:28:17,100 --> 01:28:20,799
Look at these hairline cracks,
these tyres have got to be 25 years old.

1272
01:28:20,800 --> 01:28:22,699
- What happened to the tread?
- What?

1273
01:28:22,700 --> 01:28:24,799
I said,
what happened to the tread?

1274
01:28:24,800 --> 01:28:26,299
Well, I cut it off,
thats what happened to the tread...

1275
01:28:26,300 --> 01:28:27,699
I cut it off with a carving knife...

1276
01:28:27,700 --> 01:28:30,499
otherwise it wouldn't be
a high speed tyre, would it?

1277
01:28:30,500 --> 01:28:31,899
What are you talking about?

1278
01:28:31,900 --> 01:28:35,134
Well, you've got to keep the weight in
otherwise when you get to a high speed...

1279
01:28:35,135 --> 01:28:37,799
the centrifugal force will
the tread right off, wouldn't it?

1280
01:28:37,800 --> 01:28:41,800
I run them on 65 pounds of air and
that tyre's safe up to 300 miles an hour.

1281
01:28:41,900 --> 01:28:44,499
I guarantee it. These are high
speed tyres and I made them.

1282
01:28:44,500 --> 01:28:46,699
Well, you're going to have
to replace them.

1283
01:28:46,700 --> 01:28:48,599
The suspension here is
a leaf spring...

1284
01:28:48,600 --> 01:28:49,999
I mean can we pass that?

1285
01:28:50,000 --> 01:28:53,299
Geez, last leaf spring on a motorcycle
must have been in the 1920s.

1286
01:28:53,300 --> 01:28:54,899
Well, it is 42 years old.

1287
01:28:54,900 --> 01:28:58,900
- These brakes look completely inadequate.
- Well, I'm planning on going, not stopping.

1288
01:28:58,935 --> 01:29:02,499
Well, the brakes were old
fashioned 40 years ago.

1289
01:29:02,500 --> 01:29:04,499
Is this a hinge of a gate post?

1290
01:29:04,500 --> 01:29:08,449
No, thats from an old kitchen door.

1291
01:29:08,484 --> 01:29:12,399
Let me just ask you what is this?

1292
01:29:12,400 --> 01:29:15,599
Its a cork, what does it look like?
Its a cork from a brandy bottle.

1293
01:29:15,600 --> 01:29:20,000
You know, the thing is its all about
weight. The less weight, the faster you go.

1294
01:29:20,100 --> 01:29:21,399
And where's your chute?

1295
01:29:21,400 --> 01:29:23,399
- What?
- Where's your parachute?

1296
01:29:23,400 --> 01:29:25,399
I'm not planning on bailing out.

1297
01:29:25,400 --> 01:29:27,834
No wait,
you've got to have a safety chute.

1298
01:29:27,835 --> 01:29:29,299
Well, I can't afford one.

1299
01:29:29,300 --> 01:29:32,199
These forks, if they give out we've
got ourselves some real problems.

1300
01:29:32,200 --> 01:29:35,199
I think I'd have a bit of
a problem that way, wouldn't I?

1301
01:29:35,200 --> 01:29:36,999
- Where's your fire suit?
- What?

1302
01:29:37,000 --> 01:29:38,399
Where's your fire suit?

1303
01:29:38,400 --> 01:29:40,999
Good heavens, man,
I don't intend to burst into flames.

1304
01:29:41,000 --> 01:29:43,184
Always wear me old suit pants
for good luck.

1305
01:29:43,185 --> 01:29:45,299
If they were good enough
to get married in...

1306
01:29:45,300 --> 01:29:47,899
they're good enough to ride
this old girl in and no...

1307
01:29:47,900 --> 01:29:50,199
I tuck the legs of my pants
into my socks like this...

1308
01:29:50,200 --> 01:29:53,699
stop them getting caught
in the chain and Bob's your uncle.

1309
01:29:53,700 --> 01:29:56,034
You've got your suit pants,
what are you gonna wear on top?

1310
01:29:56,035 --> 01:29:56,899
What?

1311
01:29:56,900 --> 01:30:00,099
You've got your suit pants,
what do you intend to wear on top?

1312
01:30:00,100 --> 01:30:04,500
Yes, a black woolen shirt, New Zealand
wool, water resistant, fire resistant...

1313
01:30:04,600 --> 01:30:06,899
and me bash hat.

1314
01:30:06,900 --> 01:30:09,099
Bash hat?

1315
01:30:09,100 --> 01:30:10,099
Yeah, crash helmet.

1316
01:30:10,100 --> 01:30:13,434
You're crazy, you've got to wear
at least a leather jacket on top.

1317
01:30:13,435 --> 01:30:16,734
You put the bike down on the salt,
its like coarse sand paper...

1318
01:30:16,735 --> 01:30:18,134
its going to rub
your head right off.

1319
01:30:18,135 --> 01:30:19,899
I couldn't get into the shell...

1320
01:30:19,900 --> 01:30:23,199
with anything bulkier than the shirt on
my back. Its a very tight fit in there.

1321
01:30:23,200 --> 01:30:25,399
Straight out of the ark.

1322
01:30:25,400 --> 01:30:27,599
- What did you say?
- Straight out of the ark.

1323
01:30:27,600 --> 01:30:31,099
Don't be so cheeky.
Whats your name, young man?

1324
01:30:31,100 --> 01:30:33,199
McFarlane. Mike McFarlane.

1325
01:30:33,200 --> 01:30:36,499
I knew a McFarlane, he used to sell
milking machines in Timaru.

1326
01:30:36,500 --> 01:30:40,099
You must be related to him
because he was a total prick.

1327
01:30:40,100 --> 01:30:42,399
Look here, you don't even have
a fire extinguisher installed.

1328
01:30:42,400 --> 01:30:47,000
Mike McFarlane used to give me milking
machine parts to make my sprockets with.

1329
01:30:47,100 --> 01:30:48,199
How old are you?

1330
01:30:48,200 --> 01:30:50,099
I don't know,
he was about 35 when I knew him.

1331
01:30:50,100 --> 01:30:51,299
No how old are you?

1332
01:30:51,300 --> 01:30:54,999
His brother owned a general store
down in a place called Bulls...

1333
01:30:55,000 --> 01:30:57,999
- thats a town in New Zealand.
- Sir, your machine is not safe.

1334
01:30:58,000 --> 01:31:00,999
I've been doing this for 43 years
and I'm still here to tell the tale.

1335
01:31:01,000 --> 01:31:04,399
Time's change, we started taking
airplanes instead of riding horseback.

1336
01:31:04,400 --> 01:31:06,334
- Horse power?
- Horse back. Horse back.

1337
01:31:06,335 --> 01:31:08,599
Horse back, yeah.
I got you, yeah.

1338
01:31:08,600 --> 01:31:10,299
You're too old.

1339
01:31:10,300 --> 01:31:13,234
Bollocks. I may have this saggy skin
on the outside...

1340
01:31:13,235 --> 01:31:14,899
but on the inside
I'm still 18 years old...

1341
01:31:14,900 --> 01:31:18,399
and I'll give you a run for your money,
young fella.

1342
01:31:18,400 --> 01:31:20,299
You need some help?

1343
01:31:20,300 --> 01:31:22,499
Hello.

1344
01:31:22,500 --> 01:31:25,699
Rollie Free, Marty Dickerson,
we're a couple of bike fans.

1345
01:31:25,700 --> 01:31:29,700
- Burt Munro from Kiwi land.
- Pleasure, Burt.

1346
01:31:31,000 --> 01:31:32,999
You got me good there.

1347
01:31:33,000 --> 01:31:34,699
Where are you staying?

1348
01:31:34,700 --> 01:31:36,699
Thats my salubrious
accommodation...

1349
01:31:36,700 --> 01:31:39,199
I usually sleep at night
in the back seat.

1350
01:31:39,200 --> 01:31:41,999
Salubrious you say Munro, huh?

1351
01:31:42,000 --> 01:31:43,999
We've been hearing a lot about you.

1352
01:31:44,000 --> 01:31:46,399
Sounds like you're cutting
your finances mighty fine.

1353
01:31:46,400 --> 01:31:48,099
Yeah, you could say that again.

1354
01:31:48,100 --> 01:31:50,499
We'll we're up at the Western Ridge,
why don't you drop by...

1355
01:31:50,500 --> 01:31:52,599
it looks as though you could
use a good shower...

1356
01:31:52,600 --> 01:31:55,899
and everybody's staying there and
I bet that there's a spare bed there too.

1357
01:31:55,900 --> 01:31:58,499
Thanks a lot, you yanks
are classic you know that?

1358
01:31:58,500 --> 01:32:02,500
You don't catch me that easily.

1359
01:32:06,400 --> 01:32:07,999
Hey, Burt.

1360
01:32:08,000 --> 01:32:11,299
Hello.

1361
01:32:11,300 --> 01:32:13,299
The front forks could
go at any time...

1362
01:32:13,300 --> 01:32:15,799
the suspension is right out
of the 1920s.

1363
01:32:15,800 --> 01:32:18,199
Got hairline cracks all
over his tyres...

1364
01:32:18,200 --> 01:32:21,299
he's got no fire extinguisher,
no safety chute.

1365
01:32:21,300 --> 01:32:24,899
I told you, if its a time problem, the
old guy's welcome to use some of my time.

1366
01:32:24,900 --> 01:32:27,499
Its not a time problem,
its a bike problem.

1367
01:32:27,500 --> 01:32:29,499
Well, I think we ought
to let him run.

1368
01:32:29,500 --> 01:32:31,699
He came all the way from
New Zealand to do this.

1369
01:32:31,700 --> 01:32:34,299
Jim, have you had a good look
at his machine?

1370
01:32:34,300 --> 01:32:36,399
All I know is the man's
the genuine article.

1371
01:32:36,400 --> 01:32:38,699
Yeah, but the bike is
the genuine dinosaur.

1372
01:32:38,700 --> 01:32:41,599
Look, we carry the cans
for the decisions around here.

1373
01:32:41,600 --> 01:32:44,634
And if he kills himself and there's
about a 100 to 1 that he will.

1374
01:32:44,635 --> 01:32:47,399
Are gonna have a hell
of a lot of trouble on our hands.

1375
01:32:47,400 --> 01:32:52,100
Yeah, sounds like we're a bunch
of chicken shits if you want my opinion.

1376
01:32:52,200 --> 01:32:56,200
His bike didn't even come close
to passing tech inspection, Jim.

1377
01:33:05,700 --> 01:33:07,299
Burt.

1378
01:33:07,300 --> 01:33:09,299
Hello, Jim. Come in.

1379
01:33:09,300 --> 01:33:11,199
Rollie Free said
I could find you here.

1380
01:33:11,200 --> 01:33:14,399
Rollie Free, he's the best,
he's a real gentleman.

1381
01:33:14,400 --> 01:33:18,400
He set me up in this place
for nothing.

1382
01:33:20,300 --> 01:33:21,899
What are you doing?

1383
01:33:21,900 --> 01:33:25,499
Well, the soft shoe polish
fills in the cracks makes the tyres...

1384
01:33:25,500 --> 01:33:27,899
look spick and span,
good as new.

1385
01:33:27,900 --> 01:33:29,699
Cheaper than new ones anyway.

1386
01:33:29,700 --> 01:33:33,599
I didn't see that.

1387
01:33:33,600 --> 01:33:37,600
Well? Can I run?

1388
01:33:38,400 --> 01:33:42,400
I'm sorry, Burt.

1389
01:33:46,900 --> 01:33:49,799
Who the heck
do they think they are?

1390
01:33:49,800 --> 01:33:53,399
Crikey Jim, you know, I'm not trying
to run a mile in four minutes...

1391
01:33:53,400 --> 01:33:56,299
all I've got to do is sit there
and open up the throttle...

1392
01:33:56,300 --> 01:34:00,300
I mean, after all
its my ruddy life, isn't it?

1393
01:34:00,700 --> 01:34:02,299
Can't you do anything?

1394
01:34:02,300 --> 01:34:06,900
I mean, I just want to try and get her
to go over 200 just once thas all...

1395
01:34:07,000 --> 01:34:08,899
once I've cracked 200
I'll be quite happy...

1396
01:34:08,900 --> 01:34:12,099
to piss off back home to New Zealand
and Bob's your uncle.

1397
01:34:12,100 --> 01:34:16,100
You're a well respected man around here,
can you talk to them?

1398
01:34:16,400 --> 01:34:18,399
I tried.

1399
01:34:18,400 --> 01:34:21,434
You've got as much chance
of writing yourself off as I have...

1400
01:34:21,435 --> 01:34:25,435
you know that.
Just talk to them again.

1401
01:34:25,500 --> 01:34:29,500
I know they'll listen to you, mate.

1402
01:34:30,100 --> 01:34:33,199
Okay Burt, I'll try.
See you tomorrow.

1403
01:34:33,200 --> 01:34:37,200
Okay.

1404
01:34:37,400 --> 01:34:41,400
I mean I'm half the age of some
of those characters out there.

1405
01:34:47,000 --> 01:34:48,699
Whats that?

1406
01:34:48,700 --> 01:34:52,700
Thats just indigestion.

1407
01:34:56,100 --> 01:35:01,000
Everyone wants us old buggers
to curl up in some quiet corner and die.

1408
01:35:01,900 --> 01:35:05,900
Well, Burt Munro's not ready to finish
yet, I'll tell you that, mate.

1409
01:35:08,400 --> 01:35:11,499
I'll give it a shot
but I'm not promising anything.

1410
01:35:11,500 --> 01:35:15,500
Thanks, mate.
Thanks a lot.

1411
01:35:18,800 --> 01:35:22,800
The famous Challenger One...

1412
01:35:31,700 --> 01:35:33,699
What is he doing?

1413
01:35:33,700 --> 01:35:36,599
- Didn't Jim tell him?
- He says he did.

1414
01:35:36,600 --> 01:35:39,434
- Well, then whats he doing here?
- Why won't you let him run?

1415
01:35:39,435 --> 01:35:42,199
Hey, he's too old
and his bike's too old.

1416
01:35:42,200 --> 01:35:44,699
He's come half way round the world
to ride that cycle.

1417
01:35:44,700 --> 01:35:46,199
Yeah, come on.

1418
01:35:46,200 --> 01:35:50,200
- Wendy, if he was to kill himself.
- So? Its his life.

1419
01:35:51,100 --> 01:35:52,899
Keep an eye out
for those officials.

1420
01:35:52,900 --> 01:35:55,584
You sure you want to do this?
I'm not sure its a good idea.

1421
01:35:55,585 --> 01:35:58,299
Hurry up. If we're going to do
this thing you've got to hurry.

1422
01:35:58,300 --> 01:36:02,300
Alright, lets go,
here's your helmet.

1423
01:36:02,335 --> 01:36:03,899
Here's your goggles.

1424
01:36:03,900 --> 01:36:05,899
- Come on, Burt. We've got to go.
- Yeah, right.

1425
01:36:05,900 --> 01:36:09,900
Come on, put them on.

1426
01:36:12,300 --> 01:36:16,300
Go, go, come on.

1427
01:36:17,800 --> 01:36:19,699
Okay, lets go, push.

1428
01:36:19,700 --> 01:36:21,399
Push, go fast.

1429
01:36:21,400 --> 01:36:23,199
Hey, you can't. Hey...

1430
01:36:23,200 --> 01:36:26,899
- you can't do that.
- Come on, come on!

1431
01:36:26,900 --> 01:36:30,900
Hang on!

1432
01:36:32,900 --> 01:36:36,900
Hey, where are you going with that?

1433
01:36:39,800 --> 01:36:42,699
Stop, stop, stop, stop.

1434
01:36:42,700 --> 01:36:46,199
What the hell are you doing, Burt?
What the hell are you doing?

1435
01:36:46,200 --> 01:36:48,099
Just getting her warmed up, Bob.

1436
01:36:48,100 --> 01:36:49,799
Didn't look like you were
getting her warmed up.

1437
01:36:49,800 --> 01:36:52,134
Jesus, he was going to take
the thing for a freakin' run.

1438
01:36:52,135 --> 01:36:53,251
Bob.

1439
01:36:53,252 --> 01:36:56,399
Oh, boy.

1440
01:36:56,400 --> 01:37:00,400
That is the most determined man
I have ever seen in my entire life.

1441
01:37:00,700 --> 01:37:04,199
I kind of feel sorry
for the old cooty.

1442
01:37:04,200 --> 01:37:06,199
Coming all this way.

1443
01:37:06,200 --> 01:37:08,384
Isn't there some way
we can accommodate him?

1444
01:37:08,385 --> 01:37:10,599
I mean there can't be
much risk there...

1445
01:37:10,600 --> 01:37:13,699
his bike will be
lucky if it does 70.

1446
01:37:13,700 --> 01:37:17,700
What do you say? What if we bend
the rules this once, huh?

1447
01:37:19,500 --> 01:37:23,500
Jesus!

1448
01:37:23,700 --> 01:37:25,499
Bob and I had a little chat...

1449
01:37:25,500 --> 01:37:29,500
and we're thinking we're gonna
organize a handling run for you.

1450
01:37:29,700 --> 01:37:32,899
- You are? What?
- A handling run.

1451
01:37:32,900 --> 01:37:35,234
All the officials,
we're gonna get into our vehicles and...

1452
01:37:35,235 --> 01:37:36,399
- You're joking, huh?
- No, I'm not.

1453
01:37:36,400 --> 01:37:38,499
We're going to follow
along behind you...

1454
01:37:38,500 --> 01:37:40,534
and we're going to see
if you're okay to ride this beast.

1455
01:37:40,535 --> 01:37:41,599
Of course I'm okay to ride it.

1456
01:37:41,600 --> 01:37:45,600
First thing tomorrow morning, alright?
